        <h2>Understanding Paint Correction</h2>
        <p>Paint correction is a precise process that involves leveling the clear coat to remove surface imperfections such as swirl marks, fine scratches, and oxidation. Our multi-stage approach uses progressively finer polishing compounds to achieve a flawless finish.</p>
        <p>Each vehicle is carefully assessed to determine the appropriate level of correction needed, ensuring optimal results without compromising paint thickness.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2>What's Included in Our Service</h2>
        <p>Our comprehensive package includes thorough paint decontamination, clay bar treatment, multi-stage machine polishing, and trim restoration. We also apply a protective sealant to lock in the results and provide lasting defense.</p>
        <p>Faded plastic and rubber trim is restored to its original dark, rich color using professional-grade restoration products that penetrate and protect.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
