    <h2 class="text-white">FAQs</h2>
    <div style="margin-top: var(--space-lg);">
      <details class="accordion__item">
        <summary class="accordion__trigger">How do I know if my car needs paint correction?</summary>
        <div class="accordion__content">
          <p>If you notice swirl marks, light scratches, or a dull hazy appearance in direct sunlight, your paint would benefit from professional correction.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="accordion__item">
        <summary class="accordion__trigger">Can paint correction fix deep scratches?</summary>
        <div class="accordion__content">
          <p>Paint correction can remove or significantly reduce scratches that haven't penetrated through the clear coat. Deep scratches that reach the base coat may require touch-up paint.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="accordion__item">
        <summary class="accordion__trigger">What is the best way to protect my paint after correction?</summary>
        <div class="accordion__content">
          <p>We recommend applying a ceramic or graphene coating after correction to seal in the results and provide long-lasting protection against future damage.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="accordion__item">
        <summary class="accordion__trigger">Can you restore faded plastic and rubber trim?</summary>
        <div class="accordion__content">
          <p>Yes, our trim restoration process uses professional-grade products that penetrate and rejuvenate faded plastic and rubber trim back to its original appearance.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="accordion__item">
        <summary class="accordion__trigger">How long does paint correction last?</summary>
        <div class="accordion__content">
          <p>The correction itself is permanent since it removes defects from the clear coat. When protected with a coating, your paint can stay flawless for 2 to 7+ years.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
